This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it describes a new named entity resource for person and organization names that has been compiled over seven years of large-scale multilingual news analysis combined with Wikipedia mining. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning systems to learn named entity recognition rules, which is a common topic in the field of NLP. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories due to the use of the named entity resource for improving name search in databases or on the internet and seeding machine learning systems.
